
Overview of noun apparition

The noun apparition has 4 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                     
1. (1) apparition, phantom, phantasm, phantasma, fantasm, specter, spectre -- (a ghostly appearing figure; "we were unprepared for the apparition that confronted us")
2. apparition -- (the appearance of a ghostlike figure; "I was recalled to the present by the apparition of a frightening specter")
3. apparition, phantom, phantasm, phantasma, fantasm, shadow -- (something existing in perception only; "a ghostly apparition at midnight")
4. apparition -- (an act of appearing or becoming visible unexpectedly; "natives were amazed at the apparition of this white stranger")
